#1. Write an assignment statement that creates a variable named minutes containing the number of minutes in an hour
minutes = 60 
#2. Determine the datatype of the value contained in the variable 'minutes'
type(minutes) 
#the result is <class 'int'>
#3. Write an subsequent assignment statement that updates the value in minutes by adding 5 to the current value.
more_minutes = minutes + 5
#4. Assume minutes = 1025 write a statement
print(minutes // 60, “hours”, minutes % 60, “minutes”)
